where formula_5 is the location parameter, specifying the location of the peak of the distribution, and formula_6 is the scale parameter which specifies the half-width at half-maximum (HWHM), alternatively formula_19 is full width at half maximum (FWHM). formula_6 is also equal to half the interquartile range and is sometimes called the probable error. This function is also known as a Lorentzian function, and an example of a nascent delta function, and therefore approaches a Dirac delta function in the limit as formula_21. Augustin-Louis Cauchy exploited such a density function in 1827 with an infinitesimal scale parameter, defining this Dirac delta function.

