===Multivariate Cauchy distribution===
A random vector formula_69 is said to have the multivariate Cauchy distribution if every linear combination of its components formula_70 has a Cauchy distribution. That is, for any constant vector formula_71, the random variable formula_72 should have a univariate Cauchy distribution. The characteristic function of a multivariate Cauchy distribution is given by:

